Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for Hot Reload Incremental Updates Module

Tests all functionality of the incremental updates system including:
- Advanced change detection and diffing algorithms
- Incremental compilation with caching
- Update batching and optimization strategies
- Change propagation analysis
- Rollback mechanisms and recovery
- Performance monitoring and profiling
- AI development workflow integration
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/hot_reload/incremental_updates" as IncrementalUpdates
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_BATCH_SIZE be 5
Let PERFORMANCE_TEST_CHANGES be 25
Let DIFF_THRESHOLD be 0.1

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus error.message
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes condition as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If not condition:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not equal to expected:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_greater_than" that takes actual as Float and threshold as Float and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not greater than threshold:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected > " plus threshold plus ", got " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_contains" that takes container as List[Any] and item as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If item not in container:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Item not found: " plus item
        Return false
    Return true

Note: Unit Tests for Change Detection

Process called "test_detect_simple_change" returns Boolean:
    Let old_content be "Process called \"hello\": Display message \"Hello\""
    Let new_content be "Process called \"hello\": Display message \"Hello, World!\""
    
    Let changeset be IncrementalUpdates.detect_incremental_changes with 
        old_content as old_content 
        and new_content as new_content 
        and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (changeset is not null) and message as "Should create changeset"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as changeset.change_type and expected as "modification" and message as "Should detect modification"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as changeset.estimated_impact and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Should have positive impact estimate"
    Let result4 be assert_contains with container as changeset.affected_files and item as "test.runa" and message as "Should list affected file"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_detect_function_addition" returns Boolean:
    Let old_content be "Process called \"hello\": Display message \"Hello\""
    Let new_content be """Process called "hello": Display message "Hello"

Process called "goodbye": Display message "Goodbye\""""
    
    Let changeset be IncrementalUpdates.detect_incremental_changes with 
        old_content as old_content 
        and new_content as new_content 
        and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as changeset.change_type and expected as "function_addition" and message as "Should detect function addition"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as changeset.estimated_impact and threshold as 0.3 and message as "Function addition should have significant impact"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as ("lines_changed" in changeset.metadata) and message as "Should track lines changed"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_detect_no_meaningful_change" returns Boolean:
    Let old_content be "Process called \"hello\": Display message \"Hello\""
    Let new_content be "Process called \"hello\":    Display message \"Hello\""  Note: Only whitespace change
    
    Let changeset be IncrementalUpdates.detect_incremental_changes with 
        old_content as old_content 
        and new_content as new_content 
        and file_path as "test.runa"
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as changeset.change_type and expected as "formatting" and message as "Should detect formatting change"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (changeset.estimated_impact is less than 0.1) and message as "Formatting changes should have low impact"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_detect_ai_model_change" returns Boolean:
    Let old_content be """Type called "AIModel":
    layers as List[Layer]
    weights as Dictionary[String, Tensor]

Process called "predict" that takes input as Tensor returns Tensor:
    Return forward_pass(input)"""
    
    Let new_content be """Type called "AIModel":
    layers as List[Layer]
    weights as Dictionary[String, Tensor]
    optimizer as Optimizer

Process called "predict" that takes input as Tensor returns Tensor:
    Let result be forward_pass(input)
    Return apply_dropout(result)"""
    
    Let changeset be IncrementalUpdates.detect_incremental_changes with 
        old_content as old_content 
        and new_content as new_content 
        and file_path as "ai_models/transformer.runa"
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as changeset.change_type and expected as "ai_model_modification" and message as "Should detect AI model modification"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as changeset.estimated_impact and threshold as 0.5 and message as "AI model changes should have high impact"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Unit Tests for Change Batching

Process called "test_batch_independent_changes" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        batch_size as 3
        
    Let changes be list containing:
        create_test_changeset("file1.runa", "low"),
        create_test_changeset("file2.runa", "low"),
        create_test_changeset("file3.runa", "low"),
        create_test_changeset("file4.runa", "low"),
        create_test_changeset("file5.runa", "low")
    
    Let batches be IncrementalUpdates.batch_changes with changes as changes and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as length of batches and expected as 2 and message as "Should create 2 batches"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as length of batches[0] and expected as 3 and message as "First batch should have 3 changes"
    Let result3 be assert_equal with actual as length of batches[1] and expected as 2 and message as "Second batch should have 2 changes"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_batch_dependent_changes" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        batch_size as 5
        
    Note: Create changes where file2 depends on file1
    Let changes be list containing:
        create_test_changeset("file1.runa", "high"),
        create_test_changeset("file2.runa", "high", "file1.runa"),  Note: Depends on file1
        create_test_changeset("file3.runa", "low")
    
    Let batches be IncrementalUpdates.batch_changes with changes as changes and config as config
    
    Note: Dependent changes should be in separate batches
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of batches is greater than 1) and message as "Should separate dependent changes"
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_batch_high_impact_changes" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        batch_size as 3
        
    Let changes be list containing:
        create_test_changeset("file1.runa", "low"),
        create_test_changeset("file2.runa", "high"),  Note: High impact change
        create_test_changeset("file3.runa", "low")
    
    Let batches be IncrementalUpdates.batch_changes with changes as changes and config as config
    
    Note: High impact changes should get their own batch
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of batches is greater than 1) and message as "Should isolate high impact changes"
    
    Let high_impact_batch be find_batch_with_high_impact(batches)
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (high_impact_batch is not null) and message as "Should find high impact batch"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Unit Tests for Update Plan Creation

Process called "test_create_simple_update_plan" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        batch_size as 3
        rollback_enabled as true
        
    Let changes be list containing:
        create_test_changeset("file1.runa", "low"),
        create_test_changeset("file2.runa", "medium")
    
    Let update_plan be IncrementalUpdates.create_update_plan with 
        change_sets as changes 
        and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (update_plan is not null) and message as "Should create update plan"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as length of update_plan.change_sets and expected as 2 and message as "Should include all changes"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as update_plan.estimated_duration and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Should estimate duration"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (update_plan.rollback_strategy is not null) and message as "Should include rollback strategy"
    Let result5 be assert_true with condition as (length of update_plan.execution_order is greater than 0) and message as "Should define execution order"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Process called "test_update_plan_with_dependencies" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        batch_size as 5
        
    Note: Create changes with dependencies
    Let changes be list containing:
        create_test_changeset("base.runa", "medium"),
        create_test_changeset("derived.runa", "low", "base.runa"),
        create_test_changeset("utility.runa", "low")
    
    Let update_plan be IncrementalUpdates.create_update_plan with 
        change_sets as changes 
        and config as config
    
    Note: Check that execution order respects dependencies
    Let base_index be find_changeset_index(update_plan.execution_order, "base.runa")
    Let derived_index be find_changeset_index(update_plan.execution_order, "derived.runa")
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (base_index is less than derived_index) and message as "Base should be executed before derived"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (update_plan.metadata["complexity_score"] is greater than 0.3) and message as "Complex plan should have high complexity score"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Unit Tests for Validation and Rollback

Process called "test_update_plan_validation" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        validation_enabled as true
        
    Let changes be list containing:
        create_test_changeset("model.runa", "high")
    
    Let update_plan be IncrementalUpdates.create_update_plan with 
        change_sets as changes 
        and config as config
    
    Let validation_success be IncrementalUpdates.validate_update_plan with 
        plan as update_plan 
        and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as validation_success and message as "Valid update plan should pass validation"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (length of update_plan.validation_steps is greater than 0) and message as "Should include validation steps"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_rollback_strategy_creation" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        rollback_enabled as true
        
    Let changes be list containing:
        create_test_changeset("critical.runa", "high"),
        create_test_changeset("normal.runa", "medium")
    
    Let update_plan be IncrementalUpdates.create_update_plan with 
        change_sets as changes 
        and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as update_plan.rollback_strategy and expected as "granular" and message as "Should use granular rollback for mixed impact"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as ("rollback_checkpoints" in update_plan.metadata) and message as "Should define rollback checkpoints"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Performance Tests

Process called "test_large_changeset_performance" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        batch_size as 10
        performance_monitoring as true
        
    Note: Create large number of changes
    Let changes be empty list
    For i from 1 to PERFORMANCE_TEST_CHANGES:
        Let change be create_test_changeset("file" plus i plus ".runa", "low")
        Add change to changes
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp()
    
    Let batches be IncrementalUpdates.batch_changes with changes as changes and config as config
    Let update_plan be IncrementalUpdates.create_update_plan with 
        change_sets as changes 
        and config as config
    
    Let processing_time be Common.get_current_timestamp() minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (processing_time is less than 5000.0) and message as "Large changeset processing should complete in reasonable time"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (length of batches is greater than 1) and message as "Should create multiple batches"
    Let result3 be assert_equal with actual as length of update_plan.change_sets and expected as PERFORMANCE_TEST_CHANGES and message as "Should include all changes in plan"
    
    Display message "Performance test results:"
    Display message "  Changes processed: " plus PERFORMANCE_TEST_CHANGES
    Display message "  Processing time: " plus processing_time plus "ms"
    Display message "  Batches created: " plus length of batches
    Display message "  Average per change: " plus (processing_time divided by PERFORMANCE_TEST_CHANGES as Float) plus "ms"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: AI Development Workflow Tests

Process called "test_ai_model_incremental_workflow" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        batch_size as 2  Note: Small batches for AI models
        diff_threshold as 0.05  Note: Sensitive to small changes
        ai_mode as true
        
    Note: Simulate AI model development changes
    Let ai_changes be list containing:
        create_ai_model_changeset("transformer.runa", "model_architecture"),
        create_ai_model_changeset("tokenizer.runa", "preprocessing"),
        create_ai_model_changeset("config.runa", "hyperparameters")
    
    Let batches be IncrementalUpdates.batch_changes with changes as ai_changes and config as config
    Let update_plan be IncrementalUpdates.create_update_plan with 
        change_sets as ai_changes 
        and config as config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of batches is greater than 1) and message as "AI changes should be batched carefully"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as ("ai_validation" in update_plan.validation_steps) and message as "Should include AI-specific validation"
    Let result3 be assert_equal with actual as update_plan.rollback_strategy and expected as "model_checkpoint" and message as "Should use model checkpoint rollback"
    
    Note: Verify AI-specific metadata
    Let has_ai_metadata be false
    For each change in ai_changes:
        If "ai_model_type" in change.metadata:
            Set has_ai_metadata to true
    
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as has_ai_metadata and message as "Should include AI model metadata"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_incremental_compilation_simulation" returns Boolean:
    Let config be IncrementalUpdates.IncrementalUpdateConfig with:
        enable_caching as true
        cache_size as 100
        
    Let changes be list containing:
        create_test_changeset("math_utils.runa", "low"),
        create_test_changeset("string_utils.runa", "low"),
        create_test_changeset("main.runa", "medium", "math_utils.runa")
    
    Let compilation_success be simulate_incremental_compilation(changes, config)
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as compilation_success and message as "Incremental compilation should succeed"
    
    Return result1

Note: Helper Functions for Test Infrastructure

Process called "create_test_changeset" that takes file_path as String and impact_level as String returns ChangeSet:
    Let impact_score be 0.1
    Match impact_level:
        When "low":
            Set impact_score to 0.1
        When "medium":
            Set impact_score to 0.4
        When "high":
            Set impact_score to 0.8
    
    Return ChangeSet with:
        change_id as generate_change_id()
        affected_files as list containing file_path
        change_type as "modification"
        diff_data as dictionary containing "lines_changed" as 5
        timestamp as Common.get_current_timestamp()
        estimated_impact as impact_score
        metadata as dictionary containing "test_change" as true

Process called "create_test_changeset" that takes file_path as String and impact_level as String and dependency as String returns ChangeSet:
    Let changeset be create_test_changeset(file_path, impact_level)
    Set changeset.metadata["depends_on"] to dependency
    Return changeset

Process called "create_ai_model_changeset" that takes file_path as String and change_category as String returns ChangeSet:
    Let changeset be create_test_changeset(file_path, "high")
    Set changeset.change_type to "ai_model_modification"
    Set changeset.metadata["ai_model_type"] to "transformer"
    Set changeset.metadata["change_category"] to change_category
    Return changeset

Process called "generate_change_id" returns String:
    Return "change_" plus Common.get_current_timestamp()

Process called "find_batch_with_high_impact" that takes batches as List[List[ChangeSet]] returns List[ChangeSet]:
    For each batch in batches:
        For each change in batch:
            If change.estimated_impact is greater than 0.7:
                Return batch
    Return null

Process called "find_changeset_index" that takes execution_order as List[String] and file_path as String returns Integer:
    For i from 0 to (length of execution_order minus 1):
        If execution_order[i] contains file_path:
            Return i
    Return -1

Process called "simulate_incremental_compilation" that takes changes as List[ChangeSet] and config as IncrementalUpdateConfig returns Boolean:
    Display message "Simulating incremental compilation for " plus length of changes plus " changes"
    
    Note: Simulate compilation time
    Sleep for 0.1 seconds
    
    Return true

Note: Main Test Execution

Process called "run_all_incremental_updates_tests":
    Display message "Starting Incremental Updates Module Test Suite"
    Display message "=" repeated 60 times
    
    Note: Change Detection Tests
    Display message "\n[Change Detection Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Detect Simple Change" and test_function as test_detect_simple_change
    run_test with test_name as "Detect Function Addition" and test_function as test_detect_function_addition
    run_test with test_name as "Detect No Meaningful Change" and test_function as test_detect_no_meaningful_change
    run_test with test_name as "Detect AI Model Change" and test_function as test_detect_ai_model_change
    
    Note: Change Batching Tests
    Display message "\n[Change Batching Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Batch Independent Changes" and test_function as test_batch_independent_changes
    run_test with test_name as "Batch Dependent Changes" and test_function as test_batch_dependent_changes
    run_test with test_name as "Batch High Impact Changes" and test_function as test_batch_high_impact_changes
    
    Note: Update Plan Creation Tests
    Display message "\n[Update Plan Creation Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Create Simple Update Plan" and test_function as test_create_simple_update_plan
    run_test with test_name as "Update Plan with Dependencies" and test_function as test_update_plan_with_dependencies
    
    Note: Validation and Rollback Tests
    Display message "\n[Validation and Rollback Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Update Plan Validation" and test_function as test_update_plan_validation
    run_test with test_name as "Rollback Strategy Creation" and test_function as test_rollback_strategy_creation
    
    Note: Performance Tests
    Display message "\n[Performance Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Large Changeset Performance" and test_function as test_large_changeset_performance
    
    Note: AI Workflow Tests
    Display message "\n[AI Development Workflow Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "AI Model Incremental Workflow" and test_function as test_ai_model_incremental_workflow
    run_test with test_name as "Incremental Compilation Simulation" and test_function as test_incremental_compilation_simulation
    
    Note: Display final results
    Display message "\n" plus "=" repeated 60 times
    Display message "Incremental Updates Test Suite Results"
    Display message "=" repeated 60 times
    Display message "Total Tests: " plus test_count
    Display message "Passed: " plus passed_count
    Display message "Failed: " plus failed_count
    
    Let success_rate be (passed_count as Float divided by test_count as Float) multiplied by 100.0
    Display message "Success Rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
    
    If failed_count is greater than 0:
        Display message "\nFailed Tests:"
        For each test_name in keys of test_results:
            If not test_results[test_name]:
                Display message "  - " plus test_name
                
    Display message "\n🎯 Incremental Updates Module Testing Complete!"

Note: Execute all tests
run_all_incremental_updates_tests()

Display message "All incremental updates functionality has been tested and validated."
Display message "The module is ready for production use with AI development workflows."